I lodged a complaint against you openly last time.

270
00:21:59,726 --> 00:22:01,633
Are you still holding a grudge after all this time?

271
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:05,559
I'm not thinking about you. Don't be so dramatic.

272
00:22:05,559 --> 00:22:06,959
Rise!

273
00:22:13,839 --> 00:22:14,919
Sit!

274
00:22:14,919 --> 00:22:16,937
   

275
00:22:16,937 --> 00:22:18,799
Comrades,

276
00:22:18,799 --> 00:22:25,340
it's not easy to gather all of you frontline commanders here today.

277
00:22:26,358 --> 00:22:29,640
Normally, at the scene of firefights and rescues,

278
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:33,986
people praise each and every one of you as little tigers.

279
00:22:33,986 --> 00:22:35,839
But I believe

280
00:22:35,839 --> 00:22:38,686
being just tigers isn't enough.

281
00:22:38,686 --> 00:22:41,327
I need you to become tigers with wings!

282
00:22:41,327 --> 00:22:45,079
So, today, I'm going to give you a pair of wings.

283
00:22:45,079 --> 00:22:46,979
What wings?

284
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:49,736
Theory and technology.

285
00:22:49,736 --> 00:22:53,799
Today, I have invited a talented individual from our system,

286
00:22:53,799 --> 00:22:58,177
a high-achieving student from the University of Science and Technology, Jiang Yu.

287
00:22:58,177 --> 00:23:01,986
He will talk to us about technology and theory.

288
00:23:01,986 --> 00:23:03,872
Let's give him a round of applause!

289
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:15,800
Hi, everyone. I'm Jiang Yu.

290
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,406
This guy has got an impressive background.

291
00:23:23,770 --> 00:23:27,940
What you're seeing here is something called a Super Combat Helmet.

292
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:32,711
It has a built-in computer module and a high-temperature capture camera.

293
00:23:32,711 --> 00:23:36,282
It presents information to firefighters through a specially designed augmented reality screen.

294
00:23:36,282 --> 00:23:39,820
This is a video that was released recently.

295
00:23:40,759 --> 00:23:43,657
It's called the Bipedal Robot.

296
00:23:43,657 --> 00:23:46,544
It can walk just like a human.

297
00:23:46,544 --> 00:23:51,430
It's equipped with a laser radar that can detect dense smoke and flames.

298
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,132
In recent years, there has been

299
00:23:53,132 --> 00:23:55,446
significant investment in technology within the firefighting system.

300
00:23:55,446 --> 00:23:57,666
So I believe that in the near future,

301
00:23:57,666 --> 00:24:00,999
it can replace firefighters and enter the fire scene,

302
00:24:00,999 --> 00:24:03,160
reducing our casualties.

303
00:24:06,046 --> 00:24:08,186
That's impractical.

304
00:24:10,859 --> 00:24:14,453
What frontline firefighting units need now aren't robots,

305
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:16,989
but to retain experienced personnel.

306
00:24:16,989 --> 00:24:18,573
I don't think there's a conflict

307
00:24:18,573 --> 00:24:21,720
between training experienced people and improving technology.

308
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:25,899
Advancing technology can help solve problems more quickly and efficiently.

309
00:24:25,899 --> 00:24:30,318
Advanced technology is great, and I agree with that.

310
00:24:30,318 --> 00:24:33,339
The foreign advanced technologies you mentioned aren't wrong,

311
00:24:33,339 --> 00:24:36,976
but you should also understand the practical situation at the grassroots level.

312
00:24:36,976 --> 00:24:39,612
I know that reform isn't an overnight process,

313
00:24:39,612 --> 00:24:42,882
but as long as it starts, there will be hope.

314
00:24:42,882 --> 00:24:47,052
I believe technology can solve many disputes unrelated to technology.

315
00:24:47,052 --> 00:24:48,654
Say in a fire scene,

316
00:24:48,654 --> 00:24:53,258
there's a little girl in the room on the left, and her mother is in the room on the right.

317
00:24:53,258 --> 00:24:56,295
Can your technology tell me which one to save?

318
00:24:56,295 --> 00:24:59,996
This depends on the situation at the scene and requires prediction and analysis.

319
00:24:59,996 --> 00:25:02,316
I don't need prediction and analysis.

320
00:25:02,316 --> 00:25:03,769
I'll save both.

321
00:25:03,769 --> 00:25:07,806
As long as I strengthen my training and enhance my personal skills,

322
00:25:07,806 --> 00:25:11,078
maybe I can save them both.

323
00:25:11,078 --> 00:25:13,433
Improving the technological level is certainly important,

324
00:25:13,433 --> 00:25:15,566
but we can't overlook people's abilities.

325
00:25:15,566 --> 00:25:21,022
Machines only follow commands and complete expected tasks,

326
00:25:21,487 --> 00:25:25,592
but humans can create miracles.

327
00:25:25,592 --> 00:25:27,095
Well said!

328
00:25:39,139 --> 00:25:40,839
Captain Song.

329
00:25:40,839 --> 00:25:44,543
I'd like to add you on WeChat. There's something I'd like to discuss with you.

330
00:25:44,543 --> 00:25:46,346
I'm stationed in Shili Tai Station.

331
00:25:46,346 --> 00:25:49,526
If you really want to ask me something, you can find me there.

332
00:25:52,653 --> 00:25:54,253
Captain Song...

333
00:25:56,963 --> 00:25:58,319
Here's a piece of advice.

334
00:25:58,319 --> 00:26:00,289
- Steer clear of him. 
 - Why?

335
00:26:00,289 --> 00:26:03,829
He's notorious for being argumentative. He's not a guy to mess with.

336
00:26:03,829 --> 00:26:05,865
But I find him interesting.

337
00:26:06,834 --> 00:26:08,334
Good luck.

338
00:26:15,909 --> 00:26:17,209
Come in.

339
00:26:22,910 --> 00:26:26,480
Catching you is like catching a monkey most of the time.

340
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:29,426
Everyone has already left, why are you still here?

341
00:26:31,359 --> 00:26:35,095
Division Chief Gao, I'd like to talk to you about Suo Jun.

342
00:26:35,095 --> 00:26:36,328
What about him?

343
00:26:36,328 --> 00:26:38,365
It's about his transfer application.

344
00:26:38,365 --> 00:26:40,335
Just approve it.

345
00:26:41,387 --> 00:26:43,003
You don't have to worry about me.

346
00:26:43,003 --> 00:26:44,670
I have no objections here.

347
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:47,757
Look, why do we work so hard?

348
00:26:47,757 --> 00:26:50,744
Isn't it just to ensure the safety of thousands of households?

349
00:26:50,744 --> 00:26:54,565
You see, we firefighters have to protect our own families too.

350
00:26:54,565 --> 00:26:58,519
Suo Jun's fiancée and parents

351
00:26:58,519 --> 00:27:00,018
are relying on him.

352
00:27:00,018 --> 00:27:02,698
About this application, don't let it get stuck here.

353
00:27:02,698 --> 00:27:04,689
Just approve it.

354
00:27:04,689 --> 00:27:06,937
What transfer application are you talking about?

355
00:27:06,937 --> 00:27:08,999
Suo Jun's application.

356
00:27:08,999 --> 00:27:12,573
- Didn't he give it to you? 
 - He never gave it to me at all.

357
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:28,240
Please stop taking photos.

358
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:31,459
Hurry up, please stand back. Stand back.

359
00:27:32,684 --> 00:27:34,319
It's so dangerous!

360
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:36,780
The firefighters rescued another one!

361
00:27:42,599 --> 00:27:44,399
Doctor!

362
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,160
 Requesting backup! 

363
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:26,279
 Requesting backup! 

364
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:47,100
Instructor... The instructor is still inside!

365
00:28:48,095 --> 00:28:49,582
Doctor!

366
00:28:49,582 --> 00:28:51,482
Doctor!

367
00:28:52,958 --> 00:28:54,279
Instructor!

368
00:28:54,279 --> 00:28:56,259
Instructor!

369
00:29:24,799 --> 00:29:27,200
- Thanks. 
 - Drive slowly.

370
00:29:44,070 --> 00:29:47,750
   

371
00:29:53,694 --> 00:29:55,307
Don't worry. He has been saved.

372
00:29:55,307 --> 00:29:57,129
But...

373
00:29:57,129 --> 00:30:00,698
But... his arm can't be used anymore.

374
00:32:15,802 --> 00:32:17,302
You're awake.

375
00:32:19,992 --> 00:32:22,312
Why are you wearing a sad face?

376
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:29,480
Did Division Chief Gao scold you again?

377
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:39,000
Are you worried about me?

378
00:32:45,932 --> 00:32:47,731
I'm fine,

379
00:32:49,013 --> 00:32:50,753
really.

380
00:32:53,407 --> 00:32:56,286
I didn't break any arms or legs.

381
00:32:56,286 --> 00:32:58,686
I'll recuperate and recover.

382
00:33:03,494 --> 00:33:05,459
You'll be fine.

383
00:33:07,519 --> 00:33:09,579
Stop making a sad face.

384
00:33:11,658 --> 00:33:13,258
Smile a little.

385
00:33:20,274 --> 00:33:22,527
I'll go get you the doctor.

386
00:34:02,910 --> 00:34:04,213
 You know, 

387
00:34:04,213 --> 00:34:08,440
 after I transfer, that position pays an extra ¥1,200. 

388
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:11,299
 - I can... 
 - So it's for money? 

389
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:14,612
 Do you still remember the vow we made when we formed our team? 

390
00:34:14,612 --> 00:34:16,480
 You forgot all of it, 

391
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:19,820
 abandoning your responsibilities and duties. 

392
00:34:20,427 --> 00:34:24,119
 Right now, you're a deserter! 

393
00:34:36,410 --> 00:34:39,211
 We made a vow before. 

394
00:34:39,211 --> 00:34:40,971
 Do you remember? 

395
00:34:44,349 --> 00:34:48,159
 That we would turn Shili Tai Fire Station into the best fire station in the nation. 

396
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:50,424
 What transfer application are you talking about? 

397
00:34:50,424 --> 00:34:52,924
 He never gave it to me at all. 

